The Michael Okpara University of Agriculture, Umudike (MOUAU), reflects the honesty and integrity of President Muhammadu Buhari in all its dealings both internally and externally as its visitor. Chairman of the governing council and pro-chancellor of the MOUAU, Rt Hon Lawal Zayanna stated this while speaking to newsmen at its conference hall, near Umuahia, the Abia state capital. Zayanna spoke after an emergency meeting of the council on various allegations levelled againt the management of the MOUAU and the vice chancellor (VC), Prof Francis Otunta by Drs. (Mrs) Patricia Mba and Nelson Odunze. “Mba and Amanze’s petitions were centred on illegal seizure of salary, victimization, sexual harassment, and abuse of office, and lingering and unresolved infractions in the decisions of the council respectively,” he announced. The one-time speaker of the Sokoto State House of Assembly explained that after extensive deliberations on the allegations the council found them to be frivolous, malicious, and unfounded to say the least. However, he explained that the council considered and granted two prayers by Mba that her absence from duty beyond the stipulated time frame was on health ground and the restoration of her withheld salary by the VC. Further, he maintained that the committee accepted and adopted the report of an investigation by the University Senate that Otunta did not at any time put a student in the family way and graduated her without due process. “The University after searching all her records, through the Senate, did not locate any student presently or in the past with such records. The chancellor and chairman of Senate, Otunta was not found guilty of the allegations,” he said. The chairman, who said the council passed a vote of confidence on Otunta and himself, called on the general public to disregard the allegations “which were targeted at casting assertions and damaging the image of the University.” End Sent from Yahoo Mail on Android